#DOC source=/root/yvon/docs/briefs/lifeos-reference/03--advisory-council--war-room.md strip=5% toon=4% net=8%
T|03 ·|0|The owner's "board of st advisors" — five distinct ag w/ full memory access who debate, recommend, and can be convened into a live War Room sn. The closing showcase of the walkthrough.
T|03 ·|1|
T|Purp|0|In the old sy the advisory council under-performed bc the advisor ag only had narrow knowledge of a few projects. w/ the new memory sy, five distinct ag w/ different roles get complete knowledge-base access. They produce recommendations, debate topics, surface the patterns of what the owner keeps thinking abt, and can be turned into an audio "podcast" to listen to (each ag gets a distinct HeyGen voice).
T|Purp|1|
T|Page|0|Title: Advisory Council, breadcrumb Vibe w/ AI / Advisory Council.
T|Page|1|Buttons: Set today's topic and Run a live sn (opens the War Room).
T|Page|2|Tabs/sections: Recommendations, Outcomes / rv, st Archive.
T|Page|3|
T|Toda|0|A hl recommendation, e.g. "Productize the ag-as-a-service offer now — turn the 'I run your ag' service into a fixed €2k/mo retainer, before the category name consolidates."
T|Toda|1|A proposed-by line crediting the ag(s) (e.g. a "needs your call / rv" badge).
T|Toda|2|A First step suggestion (concrete nx action), e.g. "pk the Maria engagement as the template … and pitch it to your two warmest leads this week."
T|Toda|3|An audio player — a waveform/podcast-style player (e.g. ~4:53) so the debate can be listened to rather than read. The five council ag appear as avatars under the player (hy, Nexus, Ivy, By ds, Strategist, etc.) each contributing a voice.
T|Toda|4|Action buttons on the recommendation:
T|Toda|5|Accept the proposal
T|Toda|6|Accept & cr task (push it to the Task Board / assign)
T|Toda|7|Assign to ag (delegate acting on the finding)
T|Toda|8|Ask follow-up (question the council)
T|Toda|9|Defer / Reject
T|Toda|10|
T|Reco|0|Below the hero, a stack of further recommendations (e.g. "Slow down the app-factory bet — prove By ds's retention before building #2"), each tagged (pd, st, fi…), credited to one or more council ag, w/ the same accept/assign/ask actions.
T|Reco|1|
T|Patt|0|Pattern Tracker — surfaces recurring themes the council keeps raising ("Productize, stop doing bespoke," "Focus → fewer bets, deeper," "Repackage, don't re-cr," "Get Wolf to put fi on it…"). This acts as a mirror showing the owner which topics are most ur/most discussed.
T|Patt|1|"This month" — a count/summary of topics discussed this period.
T|Patt|2|
C|Sett|0|Set today's topic / set a topic for a particular day — the owner can queue a specific question for which they want st input, framed as a debate.
C|Sett|1|Run a live sn — launches the War Room (below).
C|Sett|2|
T|War |0|A full-screen, cinematic live st room (a rendered 3D conference room — a cliffside cave w/ a round table and a city/ocean view at dusk).
T|War |1|
T|War |2|Header: WAR ROOM, a "Live sn" indicator, Pause and Skip controls, the debate topic (e.g. "shd I raise consulting rates 20% for new leads?"), and a LIVE badge.
T|War |3|Left transcript rail: a running live chat of the debate — each ag (You, Strategist, Nexus, …) speaks in turn w/ timestamped lines, arguing different angles (the data backs it / comparable founders charge more / counter-arguments abt timing, etc.).
T|War |4|Center stage: the 3D room w/ ag avatars positioned around the table (color-coded markers), and the currently-speaking ag's line captioned at the bottom.
T|War |5|The owner can jump in — an input box ("Jump in — steer the debate…") to ask questions and steer the st in real time.
T|War |6|Council recommendation popup: when the debate concludes, a card slides up — "THE COUNCIL RECOMMENDS" w/ the synthesized recommendation (e.g. "Commit now — but w/ a hard 30-day checkpoint and a defined off-ramp. Capture the upside w/o betting blind."). Actions: Accept, Accept & cr task, Back to Council.
T|War |7|
T|Agen|0|Five role-distinct advisor ag, each w/ full knowledge-base access and a unique HeyGen voice, briefed heavily on what kinds of recommendations/topics they shd cover. The output doubles as a listenable podcast.